Description: OpenFermion is an open source library for compiling and analyzing
 quantum algorithms to simulate fermionic systems, including quantum
 chemistry. Among other functionalities, this version features data structures
 and tools for obtaining and manipulating representations of fermionic and
 qubit Hamiltonians. For more information, see our release paper.
